The '''PGA National Champion Course''' is a 18-hole golf course located in Palm Beach Gardens, Florida, USA.<ref>[http://www.floridagolf.com/courses/palm-beach-gardens/pga-national-champion/ Champion Course at PGA National Resort & Spa]</ref> 

The PGA National Champion Course was opened on November 17, 1981. It was the site of the [[1983 Ryder Cup]], the [[1987 PGA Championship]] (won by [[Larry Nelson]]), and the [[Senior PGA Championship]] for 19 years, from 1982<U+2013>2000. The course underwent a $4 million renovation in December 2002, and in 2007 became the home of The [[Honda Classic]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nicklaus.com/design/pgachampion/Champion-Course-in-major-shape.php |title=PGA National's Champion Course nearly in major shape for Honda Classic |author=Dave George |publisher=Nicklaus Design, Courtesy of Palm Beach Post |date=February 28, 2012 |accessdate=May 11, 2012 }}</ref>

The course rating is 75.3 and it has a slope rating of 147 on [[Bermuda grass]].<ref>[http://www.golflink.com/golf-courses/course.aspx?course=207045 Champion Golf Course ]</ref>

